{"lemma":"لَيِسَ","slug":"لَيِسَ","root":"ل.#.س","root_slug":"ل-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-_-س","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"لَيِسْتَ","in_corpus":true,"count":64,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"لَيِسْتِ","in_corpus":true,"count":64,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"لَيِسْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"لَيِسْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"لَيِسْتُنَّ","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"لَيِسَ","in_corpus":true,"count":1342,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"لَيِسَت","in_corpus":true,"count":64,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"لَيِسا","in_corpus":true,"count":11,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"لَيِسَتا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"لَيِسُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":7,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"لَيِسْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَلْيَس","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَلْيَسِينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَلْيَسِي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَلْيَسا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَلْيَسانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَلْيَسُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَلْيَسُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَلْيَسْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَلْيَس","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَلْيَس","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَلْيَسا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَلْيَسانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَلْيَسا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَلْيَسانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَلْيَسُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَلْيَسُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَلْيَسْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"لَيِسْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"لَيِسْتُ","in_corpus":true,"count":64,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَلْيَس","in_corpus":true,"count":62,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَلْيَس","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"}],"frequency_in_corpus":1680,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لَيِسَ","root":"ليس","pos":"V","occurrence_count":89},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["adj","conj","noun","particle","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38170"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"not to be","tags":["copulative","defective"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ يَا قَوْمِ لَيْسَ بِي ضَلَالَةٌ وَلَٰكِنِّي رَسُولٌ مِن رَبِّ ٱلْعَالَمِينَ","english":"He said, “O my people, there is not error in me, but I am a messenger from the Lord of the worlds.”"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"except","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"جَاءَ النَّاسُ لَيْسَ زُهَيْرًا","english":"People came, except for Zuhayr"}]},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"Used to negate verbs","examples":[{"text":"وَلَيْسَ يَصِحُّ فِي الْأَفْهَامِ شَيْءٌ\nإِذَا ٱحْتَاجَ النَّهَارُ إِلَى دَلِيلِ\nwa-laysa yaṣiḥḥu fī l-ʔafhāmi šayʔun","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"not (refers to a preceding context)","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"أَيْنَ الْمَفَرُّ وَالْإِلَهُ الطَّالِبُ\n وَالْأَشْرَمُ الْمَغْلُوبُ لَيْسَ ٱلْغَالِبُ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be valiant, to be brave, to be courageous"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَيِسَ (layisa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine plural of أَلْيَس (ʔalyas)","tags":["form-of","masculine","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Uncertain. Traditionally taken to be a contracted pronunciation of either a verb لَيِسَ (layisa), whose ultimate origin is in turn unknown or unexplored, or of لَا (lā, “not”) + an existential أَيْس (ʔays) that has a proposed etymology in Proto-Semitic *ys < *yt. This existential would be a native cognate to Hebrew יֵשׁ (yēš) and Akkadian 𒌇 (/⁠išu⁠/, “to have or own; to be”, also used copulatively), although Al-Jallad (2018) expresses doubt that it is anything more than a back-formation from the negative, in other words implying that لَا (lā, “not”) + *أَيْس (*ʔays, existential) is just a folk etymology for لَيْسَ (laysa) from which أَيْس (ʔays) was created artificially. Al-Jallad instead proceeds to identify a form of لَيْسَ (laysa) in a Safaitic inscription dated between the first century BC and the fourth century AD, whose form, he says, invalidates the possibility of an origin in a verb لَيِسَ (layisa); he thereby argues that لَيْسَ (laysa) may either be a loan from Neo-Assyrian 𒆷𒀸𒋗 (la-aš-šu /⁠laššu⁠/, “there is not”) or from Taymanitic 𐪁𐪚𐪏 (lys³ /⁠lāʾis, lāyis⁠/, “not existing or being”)."},"ipa":["/laj.sa/","/la.ji.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38170","headword_ar":"لَيْسَ","root":"lys","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word denoting negation: (S, A, K:) it is a verb in the pret. tense, (S, A, K, Mughnee,) having no other tense, (Sb, S, M, Msb, Mughnee,) nor a part. n. nor an inf. n.; (Sb, M, Msb; *) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEila","text_ar":"فَعِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mughnee;) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layisa","text_ar":"لَيِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from which it is contracted by the suppression of a vowel, (Sb, * S, M, * K, Mughnee, *) being found difficult of pronunciation, (S,) [i. e.,] to render it easy to pronounce, (K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealoma","text_ar":"عَلْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealima","text_ar":"عَلِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, M,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"not being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S, M) because it is imperfectly inflected, being used in the pret. form for the present, (S,) [i. e.,] because it has no future, nor part. n., nor inf. n., nor derivation, wherefore, not being perfectly inflected like its coordinates, it is made like that which is not a verb, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota","text_ar":"لَيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, M:) what shows it to be a verb, (S, Mughnee,) not a particle occupying the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as Ibn-Es-Sarráj and some others after him have asserted, (Mughnee,) though not perfectly inflected like [other] verbs, (S,) is their saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasota","text_ar":"لَسْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasotumaA","text_ar":"لَسْتُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mughnee) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasotumo","text_ar":"لَسْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosaA","text_ar":"لَيْسَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosuwA","text_ar":"لَيْسُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosato","text_ar":"لَيْسَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.], (Mughnee,) like as they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabota","text_ar":"ضَرَبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarabotumaA","text_ar":"ضَرَبْتُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabotumo","text_ar":"ضَرَبْتُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]: (S:) we have not determined its measure to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is not contracted; nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEula","text_ar":"فَعُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because there is no verb of this measure with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"for its medial radical letter, except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayuw^a","text_ar":"هَيُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lusota","text_ar":"لُسْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been heard; so, accord. to this form, it may be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayuw^a","text_ar":"هَيُوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mughnee:) the Benoo-Dabbeh say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lusotu","text_ar":"لُسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lusonaA","text_ar":"لُسْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasotu","text_ar":"لَسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lasonaA","text_ar":"لَسْنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and some of them say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisotu","text_ar":"لِسْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lws","text_ar":"لوس"},{"kind":"text","text":":) but Sb says, that the Arabs did not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisota","text_ar":"لِسْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xifota","text_ar":"خِفْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lys","text_ar":"ليس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not perfectly inflected like [other] verbs. (M.) [There is also another opinion respecting its origin, which will be mentioned in the course of this article.] It [is generally a particular (not a universal) negative, and] denotes the negation of a thing at the present time; (M, Mughnee;) [i. e.] it denotes [thus] the negation of its predicate: (Msb:) and has the same government as the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its coordinates; (S;) governing the subject in the nom., and the predicate in the accus.: (S, Mughnee:) as when you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa zayodN qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"لَيْسَ زَيْدٌ قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is not a person standing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and by means of the context, it denotes the negation of a thing at a time not the present; as in the saying of El-Aashà [respecting Mohammad],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lahu naAfilaAtN maA yugib~u nawaAluhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        walayosa EaTaA='u Alyawomi maAniEahu gadaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has bounties the bestowing of which is not on alternate days; and the giving of to-day will not be a preventer of it to-morrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and [sometimes when it is followed by a verb, as] in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa xalaqa A@ll~`hu mivolahu","text_ar":"لَيْسَ خَلَقَ ا@للّٰهُ مِثْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God has not created the like of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mughnee.) But it differs from its coordinates in that the prep."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be prefixed to its predicate: as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa zayodN bimunoTaliqK","text_ar":"لَيْسَ زَيْدٌ بِمُنْطَلِقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is not going away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being a means of the verb's being trans., and also corroborative of the negation: and one may optionally not introduce it, because one may do without the corroborative, and because some verbs are trans. sometimes by means of a prep. and sometimes without a prep., as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otaqotuka","text_ar":"اِشْتَقْتُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otaqotu A_ilayoka","text_ar":"اِشْتَقْتُ اـِلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) It also differs from its coordinates in that its predicate may not be put before it: for you may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHosinFA kaAna","text_ar":"مُحْسِنًا كَانَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHosinFA layosa zayodN","text_ar":"مُحْسِنًا لَيْسَ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or some allow this latter; but others disallow it. (Ibn- 'Akeel on the Alfeeyeh, section on"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAn","text_ar":"كان"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its coordinates.) It is also used as an exceptive particle, (S, M, Mughnee,) in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mughnee;) in which case [also] its subject [which is understood] is in the nom. case, and its predicate in the accus.: (S:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='aniY","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomu layosa zayodFA","text_ar":"القَوْمُ لَيْسَ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The company of men came to me, except Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though you said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa AljaAy^iY","text_ar":"لَيْسَ الجَايِى"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2685},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodFA","text_ar":"زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M: but in the latter, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jA'nY","text_ar":"جاءنى"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataY","text_ar":"اَتَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljAy^Y","text_ar":"الجايى"},{"kind":"text","text":", we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=tiY","text_ar":"الا=تِى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You may also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='aniY Alqawomu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنِى القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosaka","text_ar":"لَيْسَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The company of men came to me, excepting thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but the separate pronoun,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAka","text_ar":"اـِيَّاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is here better. (S.) When the predicate after it is connected with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the ex. here next following, Benoo-Temeem make it in the nom. case: thus they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa AlT~iybu A_il~aA Almisoku","text_ar":"لَيْسَ الطِّيبُ اـِلَّا المِسْكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is not perfume, except musk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, nothing is perfume except musk]: which has been resolved is several ways; some holding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlTyb","text_ar":"الطيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be the subject of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lys","text_ar":"ليس"},{"kind":"text","text":": but its being peculiar to the dial. of Temeem refutes the explanations here referred to: some, again, hold"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lys","text_ar":"ليس"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be here used as a particle; and so in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa xalaqa A@ll~`hu mivolahu","text_ar":"لَيْسَ خَلَقَ ا@للّٰهُ مِثْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned above. (Mughnee.) Sometimes it is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Alt~aboriy^api","text_ar":"لَا التَّبْرِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":"which denies in a general manner to the uttermost, i. e., universally, or totally]; as is said in the K, except that in all the copies thereof we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_in~amaA","text_ar":"وَاـِنَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"put by mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warub~amaA","text_ar":"وَرُبَّمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [so in the saying in the Kur, ii. 194,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa Ealayokumo junaAHN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ عَلَيْكُمْ جُنَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA junaAHa Ealayokumo","text_ar":"لَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in verse 235 of the same chapter, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sin, chargeable upon you"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. Sometimes, also, it is used as a connective particle, (Mughnee,) in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA","text_ar":"لا"},{"kind":"text","text":"so used: (TA:) as in the saying [of a poet],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^ayona Almafar~u waAlA_il`hu AlgaAlibu\n                      \n                     \n                        waAlA^a$oramu Almagoluwbu layosa AlgaAlibu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Where is the place of flight when God is the pursuer, and El-Ashram"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning Abrahah)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the overcome, not the overcomer?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: which has been resolved by supposing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgAlb","text_ar":"الغالب"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be the subject of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lys","text_ar":"ليس"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the predicate to be suppressed; the latter being said by Ibn-Málik to be an annexed pronoun referring to El-Ashram; so that the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosahu AlgaAlibu","text_ar":"لَيْسَهُ الغَالِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the overcomer is not he"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mughnee.) It is said (M, K) by Fr, (M,) and also by Kh, (TA,) that the original of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa","text_ar":"لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^ayosa","text_ar":"لَا اَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K [in the latter of which I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo A^aSoluhu","text_ar":"اَوْ اَصْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in several copies of the K, or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo A^aSoluhaA","text_ar":"اَوْ اَصْلُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", as corrected in the TA, instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo maEonaAhu","text_ar":"اَوْ مَعْنَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the reading in the CK];) and this, says Fr, is shown by the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^o","text_ar":"جِيْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi mino A^ayosa walayosa","text_ar":"بِهِ مِنْ اَيْسَ وَلَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bring thou him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from where he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is, and is not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiytiniY mino Hayovu A^ayosa walayosa","text_ar":"اِيتِنِى مِنْ حَيْثُ اَيْسَ وَلَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come thou to me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or probably, the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiytiniY bihi","text_ar":"اِيتِنِى بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bring thou to me him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(as I find in a copy of the K, in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bh","text_ar":"به"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been added in red ink, and in the A I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iyti bihi","text_ar":"اـِيتِ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from where he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is, and he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minE Hayovu","text_ar":"مِنع حَيْثُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA wujoda","text_ar":"لَا وُجْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from where there is no finding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no being found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no existence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"no power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayosa","text_ar":"اَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawojuwdN","text_ar":"مَوْجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existing"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^ayosa","text_ar":"لَا اَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[means]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA","text_ar":"لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawojuwdN","text_ar":"مَوْجُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not found,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not existing"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and is contracted [into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa","text_ar":"لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) [but the last rendering of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ays","text_ar":"ايس"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA Ays","text_ar":"لا ايس"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to be taken from an explanation, not literal, of another saying;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yaEorifu","text_ar":"مَا يَعْرِفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayosa mino layosa","text_ar":"اَيْسَ مِنْ لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he knows not a thing existing from a thing not existing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] Aboo-'Alee relates, that Sb said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^o bihi mino Hayovu walayosaA","text_ar":"جِيْ بِهِ مِنْ حَيْثُ وَلَيْسَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bring thou him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, from where he,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, is and is not"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walayosa","text_ar":"وَلَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the fet-hah of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"being made full in sound, on account of the pause. (M.) In the saying of a certain poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado rus~ati AlHaAjaAtu Einoda qayosi\n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*o laA yazaAlu muwlaEFA bilayosi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wants have been forgotten as old things"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rus~at","text_ar":"رُسَّت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained in the M, as used here, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rs","text_ar":"رس"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with Keys, since he ceases not to be addicted to"},{"kind":"text","text":"the use of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the word leysa"},{"kind":"text","text":"], it is made by him a noun, and declined. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","Sb","M","Msb","TA"]}]}}